(7x^2 + 2x − 7)/(x^3 − x)
\dfrac{5x^2+2x-9}{x^3-x^2-6x}
x^3-x^2-6x = x(x-3)(x+2)
\dfrac{5x^2+2x-9}{x^3-x^2-6x}
\dfrac{A}{x}+\dfrac{B}{x-3}+\dfrac{C}{x+2}
A,B,C
\dfrac{5x^2+2x-9}{x^3-x^2-6x} = \dfrac{A}{x}+\dfrac{B}{x-3}+\dfrac{C}{x+2} \\ \Longrightarrow 5x^2+2x-9=A(x-3)(x+2)+Bx(x+2) +Cx(x-3) \\ \Longrightarrow 5x^2+2x-9= Ax^2-Ax-6Ax +Bx^2+2Bx +Cx^2-3Cx \\ \Longrightarrow 5 = A+B+C\\ \phantom{\Longrightarrow\ } 2 = -A+2B-3C \\ \phantom{\Longrightarrow\ } -9 = -6A
A = \frac{3}{2}
B = \frac{14}{5}
C = \frac{7}{10}
\dfrac{3}{2}\cdot\dfrac{1}{x} + \dfrac{14}{5}\cdot\dfrac{1}{x-3}+\dfrac{7}{10}\cdot\dfrac{1}{x+2}
